{"id":"project-LICHEN-7qbw","title":"Routing request_id not properly extracted from RouteRequest variant","description":"File: rust/lichen-meshtastic/src/bridge.rs:222-252

In process_incoming's handling of RoutingApp, the RouteRequest variant is not handled:

```rust
match routing.variant {
    Some(routing::Variant::ErrorReason(e)) => { ... }
    Some(routing::Variant::RouteReply(id)) => { ... }
    _ => Ok(IncomingResult::RoutingResponse {
        request_id: data.request_id,  // Uses Data.request_id, not the routing message's id
        error: None,
    }),
}
```

The catch-all arm handles RouteRequest but uses data.request_id instead of extracting the id from the RouteRequest variant itself. Per Meshtastic protocol, RouteRequest contains its own request ID.

IMPACT: RouteRequest packets will have their request_id misinterpreted, potentially causing routing request/response correlation failures.

FIX:
```rust
Some(routing::Variant::RouteRequest(id)) => {
    Ok(IncomingResult::RoutingResponse {
        request_id: id,
        error: None,
    })
}
